obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (71722)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 42
  title `Indian Penal Code to apply to offences committed previous to 1st January, 1862.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71722&sectionno=39&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), with the exception of Chapter VI, shall be applicable to`
  line `all offences committed before first January, 1862, in territory which was, at the time of the commission of`
  line `such offence, subject to the State Government of the Punjab:---`
  line
  line `Saving of privileges conferred on certain Chiefs.--Provided that nothing contained in this section`
  line `shall affect any privilege conferred on certain Chiefs in the Punjab by the Central Government, or by the`
  line `Board of Administration for the affairs of the Punjab, nor any indemnity or pardon granted by competent`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_a:
  sectionId (71739)
  sectionNo 39-A
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to establish system of village-watchmen, and municipal-watchmen and to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71739&sectionno=39-A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[Power to establish system of village-watchmen, and municipal-watchmen and to make rules.----The State Government may establish a system of village-watchmen or municipal-watchmen in any`
  line `part of the territories under its administration, and in furtherance of this object may, from time to time, make`
  line `rules to provide for the following matters:`
  line
  line `(a) the definition of the limits of watchmen's beats;`
  line
  line `(b) the determination of the several grades of watchmen, and the number of each grade to be`
  line `appointed to each beat;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment, suspension, dismissal and resignation of watchmen of each grade;`
  line
  line `(d) the equipment and discipline of, and the control and supervision over, such watchmen;`
  line
  line `(e) the conferring upon them, and the exercise by them, of any powers and the enjoyment by them`
  line `of any protection or privilege, which may be exercised and enjoyed by a police-officer under any law`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(f) the performance by them of such duties relating to police, sanitation or statistics, or for the benefit`
  line `of the village communities or municipalities within their respective beats, as the State Government thinks`
  line fit;
  line
  line `(g) the exercise of authority over, and the rendering of aid to, such watchmen by headmen of the`
  line `villages or members of the Municipal Committees of the towns comprised in their respective beats;`
  line
  line `(h) the performance, by the headmen of villages comprised in the beat of any watchmen, of any of`
  line `the duties of a village-watchman in aid of, or substitution for, such watchman;`
  line
  line `(i) the exercise, by such village-headmen for the purposes referred to in clauses (g) and (h), or by`
  line `members of Municipal Committees for the purposes referred to in clause (g) of this section, of any of`
  line `the powers, and the enjoyment by such headmen or members of any privilege or protection, of a villagewatchman, or a municipal-watchman, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(j) the determination of the rate at which, and the mode in which, watchmen shall be paid, and, in`
  line `the case of village-watchmen, of the mode in which their pay, the expenses of their equipment, and other`
  line `charges connected with the village-watchman-system shall be provided for, whether out of cesses or funds`
  line `already leviable or available in the villages comprised in the beat, or by a special tax in money or kind to`
  line `be imposed on any class of persons residing or owning property in, or resorting to, such villages, or partly`
  line `in one of these ways and partly in the other;`
  line
  line `(k) the collection with or without the aid of the village-headmen, and by any process available for`
  line `the realisation of the land-revenue, of any tax imposed under clause (j) of this section, and the application`
  line `of, and the mode of accounting for, the same; and generally for`
  line
  line `(l) the efficient working of the system of village-watchmen or municipal-watchmen:`
  line
  line Provided---
  line
  line `first, that the rules to be made regarding the appointment of village-watchmen shall allow to the`
  line `headmen of the villages comprised in the beat to which such a watchman is to be appointed a power of`
  line `nomination to be exercised in such manner and subject to such reasonable conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by such rules;`
  line
  line `secondly, that the rules to be made under clause (j) of this section with regard to village-watchmen`
  line `shall include provisions for recording and securing due consideration of the views and opinions on the`
  line `matters therein referred to of the headmen of the villages comprised in each beat.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_b:
  sectionId (71740)
  sectionNo 39-B
  orderNo 44
  title `Obligation to assist watchmen and headmen. Person obstructing watchman or headman may be arrested without warrant`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71740&sectionno=39-B&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_b_content:
  string
  line `39-B. Obligation to assist watchmen and headmen.— Every person is bound to render to a villagewatchman, or municipal watchman, or village-headman discharging the duties of a police-officer under the`
  line `rules made hereunder, all the assistance which he is bound to render to a police-officer.`
  line
  line `Person obstructing watchman or headman may be arrested without warrant.—Any person who`
  line `obstructs such watchman or headman in the discharge of such duties may be arrested without warrant by a`
  line `police-officer or by any watchman or village-headman empowered in this behalf by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_c:
  sectionId (71741)
  sectionNo 39-C
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to direct local taxation for payment of police enrolled under Act 5 of 1861.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71741&sectionno=39-C&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[39-C. Power to direct local taxation for payment of police enrolled under Act 5 of 1861.—`
  line `Whenever it seems to the State Government expedient that the duties of watch-and-ward and other internal`
  line `police-service of any town or village not comprised within the limits of a municipality or within the limits`
  line `of a village-watchman's beat as defined under the power conferred by section 39-A should be performed by`
  line `police-officers enrolled under ^2Act 5 of 1861, the State Government may direct that the said service shall be`
  line `so performed, and may also ^3*** direct that the charges for the time being fixed by such Government on`
  line `account of such service shall be defrayed by taxes to be levied in such town or village.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1875, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. The Police Act.`
  line
  line `3. The words “subject to the control of the G.G. in C.” repealed by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_d:
  sectionId (71742)
  sectionNo 39-D
  orderNo 46
  title `Notice of taxes proposed to be levied. Objections to taxation. Procedure thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71742&sectionno=39-D&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_d_content:
  string
  line `39-D. Notice of taxes proposed to be levied.-- When the State Government has, under section 39-C,`
  line `directed that taxes shall be levied in any town or village, the Deputy Commissioner may from time to time`
  line `issue a public notice in such town or village explaining the nature of the taxes he proposes to levy.`
  line
  line `Objections to taxation.--- Any inhabitant of such town or village objecting to the taxation thus proposed`
  line `may, within fifteen days from the publication of such notice, send his objection in writing to the Deputy`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `Procedure thereon.--- After the expiry of fifteen days from the publication of the notice, the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner may submit for the information of the State Government a report of the proposal made by`
  line `him. Such report shall contain specific mention of the objections (if any) urged to his proposal and his`
  line `opinion on such objections.`
  line
  line `No such tax shall be levied until it has, upon such report, been approved by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_e:
  sectionId (71743)
  sectionNo 39-E
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to fix rates of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71743&sectionno=39-E&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_e_content:
  string
  line `When any such tax has been so approved by the State Government,`
  line `the Deputy Commissioner may from time to time, subject to such rules consistent with this Act as the State`
  line `Government may from time to time prescribe, determine the rates at which it is to be levied.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_e_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_f:
  sectionId (71744)
  sectionNo 39-F
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make rules for collection of taxes`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71744&sectionno=39-F&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_f_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may from time to time`
  line `make rules to provide for the collection of such taxes by any process available for the realisation of the landrevenue and to regulate the application and mode of accounting for the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_f_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_g:
  sectionId (71745)
  sectionNo 39-G
  orderNo 49
  title Repealed..
  content `Repealed by the Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71745&sectionno=39-G&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_39_g_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (71723)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 50
  title `State Government may confer powers of police-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1878, s. 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71723&sectionno=40&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, if it thinks`
  line `fit, confer on any person any of the powers which may be exercised by a police-officer under any Act for`
  line `the time being in force, ^1and may withdraw any powers so conferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (71724)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 51
  title `Trackers may call for assistance in carrying on tracks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71724&sectionno=41&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `When an offence is, has been, or may`
  line `reasonably be supposed to have been committed, and the tracks of the persons who may reasonably be`
  line `supposed to have committed such offence, or of any animal or other property reasonably supposed to be`
  line `connected with such offence, are followed to a spot within the immediate vicinity of a village, the person`
  line `following such tracks may call upon any headman or village-watchman in such village to assist in carrying`
  line `on the tracks.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (71725)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 52
  title `Penalty for withholding assistance or conniving at offence or escape.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Punjab Adaptations of Laws (State and Concurrent Subjects) Order, 1968 (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71725&sectionno=42&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If such headman or`
  line `watchman do not forthwith give such assistance, or if the inhabitants of such village do not afford full`
  line `opportunity for search in their houses for the offenders, or, if from the circumstances of the case, there shall`
  line `appear good reason to believe that the inhabitants of such village, or any of them were conniving at the`
  line `offence or at the escape of the offenders, and such offenders cannot be traced beyond the village, the`
  line `Magistrate of the district may, with the previous sanction of the Commissioner of the Division inflict a fine`
  line `upon such village not exceeding five hundred rupees, except in the case of stolen property over five hundred`
  line `rupees in value, in which case the fine shall not exceed the value of such property.`
  line
  line `Appeal to High Court.—An appeal against all convictions under this section shall lie to the High Court`
  line `of Punjab ^1and Haryana.`
  line
  line `Fine may be awarded to injured parties, and fee to tracker.—The Magistrate may direct that the fine`
  line `imposed under this section or any part thereof shall be awarded to any persons injured by such offence in compensation for such injury; and, in the case of stolen property recovered through the agency of a tracker,`
  line `may direct that such property be not restored to its owner until he has paid to such tracker such fee, not`
  line `exceeding one-fourth part of the value of the stolen property, as the said Magistrate seems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (71726)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 53
  title `Control of slaughter of kine and sale of beef.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. The words “with the consent and” omitted by Act 12 of 1878, s. 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71726&sectionno=43&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The slaughter of kine and the sale of beef shall`
  line `not take place except ^1* * * subject to rules to be from time to time, either generally or in any particular`
  line `instance, prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (71727)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 54
  title `Control of entry into towns of bands of armed men.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. The words “with the consent and” omitted by Act 12 of 1878, s. 6`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71727&sectionno=44&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No band of armed men shall enter into any`
  line `city or town, except ^1* * * subject to rules to be from time to time, either generally or in any particular`
  line `instance, prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (71728)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 55
  title `Powers of Magistrate of district as to foreign vagrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71728&sectionno=45&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate of the district may, if`
  line `he considers that any band of foreign vagrants is likely to occasion a breach of the peace or to commit any`
  line `offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), prohibit such band from entering his district; or, if they`
  line `are already in his district, may require them within a given time to leave it.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (71729)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 56
  title `Surveillance, etc., of band failing to comply with Magistrate's order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71729&sectionno=46&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `If any such band fail to`
  line `comply with the orders of the said Magistrate within the prescribed period, he shall report the matter to the`
  line `State Government, and the State Government may give such directions for the surveillance, control or`
  line `deportation of such band as to it seems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (71730)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 57
  title `Crossing of streams on buoys or skins.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. The words “with the consent and” omitted by Act 12 of 1878, s. 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71730&sectionno=47&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `No person shall cross any river or stream on a buoy or`
  line `inflated skin, nor shall have in his possession or custody any buoy or skin for the purpose of being used in`
  line `crossing any river or stream, except ^1* * * subject to rules to be from time to time, either generally or in`
  line `any particular instance, prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (71731)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 58
  title `Use of pasturage or natural product of Government land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950 for “the Govt. for whose purposes the land is vested in His Majesty”.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71731&sectionno=48&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `No person shall make use of the`
  line `pasturage or other natural product of any land being the property of the Government, except with the consent`
  line `and subject to rules to be from time to time, either generally or in any particular instance, prescribed`
  line `by ^1the Government concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (71732)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 59
  title [Replead.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71732&sectionno=49&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Repealed by the Opium Act, 1878 (1 of 1878), Section 2 and`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (71733)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power to make rules as to matters mentioned in Sections 43 to 48.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71733&sectionno=50&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `^1[50. Power to make rules as to matters mentioned in sections 43 to 48.—The State Government may`
  line `from time to time make rules as to the matters mentioned in ^2sections 43 to 48 inclusive.`
  line
  line `Existing rules.—All existing rules upon such matters, which might have been made under this section`
  line `had it been in force, shall be deemed to have been made hereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1875,s. 3, for section 50.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and Schedule II, for “sections forty-three to forty-nine”.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_a:
  sectionId (71746)
  sectionNo 50-A
  orderNo 61
  title `Conditions of validity of rules hereafter made under this Act`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71746&sectionno=50-A&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_50_a_content:
  string
  line `50-A. Conditions of validity of rules hereafter made under this Act.--^1[(1)] ^2[Rules made under this`
  line `Act shall not be valid unless:]---`
  line
  line `(a) they are consistent with the laws for the time being in force in the ^3[territories to which this Act`
  line extends];
  line
  line `(b) they are published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `^4[* * *]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937 for All rules hereafter made by the L.G. under any power conferred by this Act shall be subject to the`
  line `control of the G.G. in C. and no such rules shall be valid unless.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by for States of Punjab and Delhi by 2 A.L.O., 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `4. Clause (c) of Section 50-A repealed by Act 4 of 1914.`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, Section 2 and Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_b:
  sectionId (71747)
  sectionNo 50-B
  orderNo 62
  title `Penalties for breach of such rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71747&sectionno=50-B&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_50_b_content:
  string
  line `50-B. Penalties for breach of such rules.—The State Government may, in making any rule under any`
  line `of the powers conferred by this Act, attach to the breach of it, in addition to any other consequences that`
  line `would ensue from such breach, a punishment on conviction before a Magistrate not exceeding six months'`
  line `imprisonment, or three hundred rupees fine, or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (71734)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 63
  title `Republication of rules and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Punjab Act 1 of 1910, for the original Section 51.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71734&sectionno=51&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[51. Republication of rules and orders. All rules which the State Government is empowered to`
  line `issue under this Act, and all circulars issued by the High Court of Punjab ^2and Haryana, shall be republished`
  line `from time to time by the State Government, and upon such republication, shall be arranged in the order of`
  line `their subject-matter, and all such alterations or amendments as may have been made since the last preceding`
  line `publication thereof, or may have become necessary or advisable, shall be embodied therewith, and upon`
  line `such republication all such rules and circulars previously issued shall be repealed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (71735)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 64
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repealed by the Northern India Takkavi Act, 1879 (10 of 1879).]`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109&sectionId=71735&sectionno=52&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00101_187204_1663830323109
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
